CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F307A1780481194
OL,3,CHome Secretary warns against division
OL,4,Cover Henry Nowak murder
OL,6,FMs Mahmood said one officer had
OL,7,Falready been misidentified and had to
OL,8,Fmove out of his home to protect
OL,9,Fhimself and his family after receiving
OL,10,Fdeath threats.
OL,12,FAccording to Police and Crime
OL,13,FCommissioner Donna Jones, a "central"
OL,14,Fpart of this crime was Digwa's ability
OL,15,F"to carry a knife in public" due to
OL,16,Fthe exemption given to carrying
OL,17,Fceremonial daggers.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,308,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30706
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F307A1780481194
OL,3,CHome Secretary warns against division
OL,4,Cover Henry Nowak murder
OL,6,FReferencing the calls to "limit the
OL,7,Fright of Sikhs to carry their
OL,8,Fceremonial knives", the Home Secretary
OL,9,Fsaid "carrying a knife for the purpose
OL,10,Fof religious observance is one thing"
OL,11,Fbut condemned its use in this "vile
OL,12,Fact".
OL,14,FIn response, Chris Philp, the Shadow
OL,15,FHome Secretary criticised the police
OL,16,Fresponse and claimed that "the
OL,17,Fdangerous ideology of so-called anti-
OL,18,Fracism" allowed people to be treated
OL,19,Fdifferently.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,308,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30707
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F307A1780481194
OL,3,CHome Secretary warns against division
OL,4,Cover Henry Nowak murder
OL,6,FHe urged the Home Secretary to
OL,7,Fwithdraw the police's "so-called anti-
OL,8,Fracism commitment", labelling it as
OL,9,F"morally wrong".
OL,11,FLiberal Democrat home affairs
OL,12,Fspokesperson, Max Wilkinson, welcomed
OL,13,Fthe Home Secretary's comments and
OL,14,Fsupported police officers saying: "We
OL,15,Frely on their good judgement every
OL,16,Fday" and highlighted that "Digwa
OL,17,Fbetrayed his faith".
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
